cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 

- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the comparison between NOMA and MU-MIMO, which involves information theory concepts such as channel capacity and modulation schemes. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper proposes methods to improve the efficiency of NOMA-based transmission, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses techniques to improve the energy efficiency and end-to-end transmission delay of NOMA-based systems, which involves system optimization and control. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the implementation complexity and delay of NOMA-based transmission, which is related to multimedia systems. 
- cs.COM (Computer Communications and Networks): The paper discusses the user pairing complexity and the cost of hybrid automatic repeat request, which are related to computer communications and networks.
